Benign (3 a.m. ET) trade comments out of China caused a -12 handle drop in S&P futures to reverse and, at around 6:15 a.m. ET, are back to +26 handles. That's a near 40-handle reversal from the early morning's lows!

As most are aware, I have expected a large asset allocation to favor equities (beginning yesterday and, perhaps into Friday's trading). So far so good, as including the overnite futures action, the accumulated gain in the S&P index already exceeds forty points.
